---
description: Project rules for isometric-berlin
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repository root in full before suggesting any
change. It is the single source of truth for scope, data sources,
licensing, pipeline steps, and forbidden actions. The same rules apply
to Cursor, Codex, Claude Code, Gemini CLI, and Perplexity.

Non-negotiables:

- Scope: Berlin Regierungsviertel only (v0.1). See `AGENTS.md §3`.
- Data: Berlin LoD2 (`dl-de/zero-2-0`) + OpenStreetMap (`ODbL`) only.
  No Google Maps / Google Tiles API. See `AGENTS.md §4` and `§11`.
- Tooling: `uv` for Python, `bun` for the viewer. No `pip`, `poetry`,
  `conda`, `npm`, or `pnpm`.
- Attribution overlay must remain visible in the viewer:
  "© OpenStreetMap contributors · 3D building models: Geoportal Berlin (dl-de/zero-2-0)".
- Static-only viewer build, Perplexity-hosting friendly: relative
  paths, `vite base: './'`, total bundle < 200 MB.

Commit messages: `step-<n>: <short imperative>`, where `<n>` is the
pipeline step number from `AGENTS.md §5`.

When unsure, stop and ask the owner. Scope discipline beats velocity.
